18
December
UBA Ghana launched new and upgraded e-products

As part of efforts to position UBA as the electronic bank of Ghana, UBA Ghana, has rolled out a number of e-products targeted at corporate businesses and individuals. These products range from online web acquiring solutions- (U- collect and U-bills), Cards (visa gold, Africard, smart money), Corporate online banking (U-Direct, U- Pay HR), POS Terminals (Visa/Mastercard POS) to Remittances (africash sub agents roll out).

Speaking at the launch of these products, Head of products sales, Johnson Olakunmi, indicated that, U-Direct Corporate is an integrated product which allows corporate customers to manage their cash and banking transactions, cash flows, balance reporting, corporate mobility and supply chain.

On the Point of Sale Terminals, Mr. Olakunmi explained that, this is a portable device that facilitates the payment of goods and services at various merchant locations across the country using UBA payment cards.

Elucidating on the U-Collect and U-Bills offerings, Mr. Olakunmi indicated U-Collect is a consolidated internet gateway that uses cards while the U-Bills is an internet platform that enables merchants collect bill payments online. With these platforms, customers of the bank have 27/4 access to online payments.

Also rolled out at the launch was the new UBA Visa Gold card. This is a premium debit card with enhanced transactional limits and value.

In demonstration of UBA appreciation to its customers, two promotions that rewards customers for using UBA’s electronic and online products were rolled out. These were the cashlite promotion and the “Aky3di3 nkoaa” promotion that rewards customers for receiving their remittances in any UBA branch across the country.

04
December
UBA SUPPORTS GHANA EXPORT PROMOTION AUTHORITY TO ORGANIZE THE 24TH NATIONAL AWARDSFOR EXPORT ACHIEVEMENTS.


United Bank for Africa (UBA) once again demonstrated its commitment to promoting Ghanaian businesses; as it presented a cheque of Nine Thousand Ghana Cedis (Ghs9,000.00) to the Ghana Export Promotion Authority in support of t he 24th National Awards for Exports Achievement for 2013.

The presentation of the cheque took place at the launch of this year’s award; which seeks to recognize and reward exporters who have distinguished themselves in the past year.

Presenting the awards, the Deputy Managing Director of UBA, Mr. Usman Isiaka reiterated UBA’s commitment to promoting export and facilitating trade across Africa through its AFRITRADE service and AFRICARD product. He indicated that, in addition to the cheque,‘ UBA will offer all fifteen winners free UBA prepaid cards with preloaded token amount on each card to facilitate their subsequent use as cash advance, travel advance and expense management cards bothlocally and internationally’.

The Deputy Minister of Trade and Industry, Mr Ibrahim MurtalaMuhammed who received the cheque on behalf of GEPA expressed his profound gratitude to UBA and commended the bank for this laudable initiative. He indicated that, government would have had to finance this event; but this support from UBA will go a long way to ease government’s financial burden. He then charged other corporate institutions to emulate UBA’s effort.

The awards ceremony has been slated for October 17, 2014 at the Banquet Hall of the State House.
04
December
UBA GHANA (BABY CRYING) WINS CIMG RADIO ADVERT OF THE YEAR-2013

The radio advert of UBA Ghana; known as Baby Crying, was adjudged the Radio Advertof The Year-2013 at the 25th Chartered Institute of Marketing Ghana (CIMG) Awards; held on Saturday October 18, 2014 at the Banquet Hall of the State House.


The award, a trophy and citation were presented to The Deputy Managing Director, Mr. Usman Isiaka; supported by the Regional Director, Mr. Charles Odonkor, Head of Corporate Communications, Mrs. Linda Narh, Nii Amponsah Quainoo of the Corporate Communications Department and representatives from the advertising agency; Origin8.

The citationacknowledges the excellent combination of creativity and imagination based on strong consumer insight;which positions UBA Ghana as the bank that offers its customers the peace of mind to go about their businesses as UBA takes care of their concerns.

The effectiveness of the message in the radio advert is perfectly captured in the citation which according to CIMG “…recognizes your creativity at holding your audience captive with the message and duly confers on UBA Baby Crying- Radio Advert of the year-2013”.

The CIMG Awards is an annual professional marketing awards that seeks to recognize organizations and individuals who have distinguished themselves. While nominations are opened to the general public, selection and conferment of the award is based on the decision of a panel of judges comprising experts from the industry.

03
July
UBA Ghana engages experts in a Trade Forum

UBA Ghana held its first Bi-Annual Trade Conference at the plush Golden Tulip Hotel in Accra with the aim of creating opportunity for business leaders in Ghana and across Africa to deliberate on the importance of intra-trade activities. The Conference which was held under the theme, “Driving Regional Trade through Strategic Partnerships.”  was well attended by corporate Ghana .  Mrs. Abiola Bawuah MD/CEO of UBA Ghana in her welcome address noted that intra-African trade has enormous potential to create employment, propel investment and foster growth in the African continent.

Mrs. Abiola Bawuah averred that although African countries have made several efforts to exploit potentials of trade development, coupled with political commitments, intra-Africa trade links are “pitifully weak.” “Only about 12% is with other Africa countries. By comparison 70% of Europe’s trade is with its own continent. The same is true in Asia. In North America the figure is 40%,” she said. She also indicated that intra-Africa trade is far below its potential due to poor infrastructure, cost of doing business, limited role of private sector among others.

The Minister for Trade and Industry, Hon Haruna Iddrisu, in a statement read on his behalf by Mr. Anthony Nyame Baafi Director, Regional, Multilateral Trade at the Trades Ministry, said there is a strong harmony among African leaders that regional integration is indispensable to unlock economies of scale and sharpen competitiveness. However, he indicated that in spite of efforts to introduce free trade areas with customs unions and common markets within the African region, the level of intra-African trade remains relatively low as compared to other continents across the world. The Minister also agreed to the fact that some circumstances hinder the realisation of intra-African trade. According to him, lack of resources and production between many African countries and low levels of incomes and investments accounted for the situation. “Trade tariffs remain high on products of export interest to regional partners, and non-tariff barriers are pervasive across the continent. In particular land locked countries face very high trade costs and more daunting challenges to increasing their share of trade in the region,” he said.

The Trades Minister also stated that although ECOWAS implemented a sub-regional Trade Liberalization Scheme (ETLS) to grant free-flow of goods from one country to the other, Africa continues to face serious bottlenecks which make it difficult for it to achieve full positive results from trade and investment potentials.

According to him, effective implementation of trade facilitation as a tool for driving Regional Trade is key to achieving intra-African trade and that it has a huge potential for businesses like the UBA, governments and consumers.

Hon. Haruna Idrissu also averred that working towards effective and efficient trade facilitation will help reduce bureaucracy and will broaden market access, increase small scale and medium enterprises participation in international trade and reduce corruption. He however called on African countries to strengthen their competitiveness by enacting policy reforms to ensure more competitive markets for transport and trade facilitation.

Presenting a paper on the topic, ‘Facilitating Trade Within Africa,’ The Deputy Managing Director of UBA, Mr. Isiaka Usman said the whole idea of regional trade will inure enormous benefits to countries as it will create employment opportunities, ensure the use of African currencies for trade settlements at lower costs and strengthen real regional integration.

14
March
Mr. Kwame Pianim Retires from UBA Board.

Mr. Kwame Pianim Retires from UBA Board.

The  pioneer Chairman of UBA Ghana, Mr. Kwame Pianim has retired from the board and has been succeeded by Mr. Kenneth Orji, a London School of Economics trained veteran banker and consultant.

The new Chairman of UBA Ghana, Directors of UBA Ghana and Group Managing Director/CEO spoke glowingly about  Mr. Pianim acknowledging his simplicity, principled ways, foresight and role in the birthing of UBA Ghana almost a decade ago at the Send forth ceremony held in his honour at the Africa Regents Hotel in Accra.  

“Under your watch, UBA Ghana has grown to be our best performing country subsidiary and its quiet impressive how seamlessly you have managed to combine business development, risk management and corporate governance to turn out these superlative performances. You are a visionary leader and we have learnt so much from you over the years. We wish you well in your new endeavours and will continue to tap into your reservoir of knowledge” said Phillips Oduoza MD/CEO in his remarks.  

Professor Kwamena Ahwoi described Mr. Pianim as the Mandela of Ghana, adding that his ability to forgive his opponents and colleagues is remarkable. He also “Inflexibly principled and wise” said Prof Ahwoi. It is amazing how he has managed to combine “risk management, governance and business together, something most individuals find it elusive,” he added.  

Mr. Pianim thanked the Group for the opportunity to lead the Board of UBA Ghana. He acknowledged the tenacity push and determination of the former MD/CEO,UBA Mr. Tony Elumelu to establish UBA Ghana in 2004 and commended the Group for its support. He also paid glowing tribute to Mr. Paul Acquaah, the former Governor of the bank of Ghana who granted the license, against popular sentiments at the time.  

Mr. Uduoza together with Mr. Kennedy Uzoka, DMD and Mrs. Abiola Bawuah, MD/CEO UBA Ghana presented a letter of appreciation together with gifts items to Mr. Pianim, as a token of appreciation for his contribution towards the success of the bank.  

The event brought together captains of industries, bankers, politicians and some senior citizens from the financial institutions in Ghana.  

Andrews Kwame Pianim is a celebrated Ghanaian Business economist and Investment consultant. He attended Achimota School, Ghana and holds a B.A Double Honours in Economics and Political Science from the University of New Brunswick, Canada and M.A in Economics from Yale University USA.  

 New Board Chairman Mr. Kenneth Orji

Mr. Orji was educated at University of Ibadan, Nigeria where he was a J. F. Kennedy Scholar, having emerged national first place winner of the John F. Kennedy Memorial Essay Contest, organized by the US Government. He graduated with BSc Hons. and was awarded the Sir James Robertson Prize and Medal for Outstanding Performance in Economics. He also obtained MSc Accounting and Finance from London School of Economics and attended Harvard Business School (Program for Management Development).                                     

Mr. Orji has over 33 years experience, primarily in banking and finance, human capital development, consulting and advisory services.  

He began his banking career at International Merchant Bank Limited, Nigeria(affiliate of First National Bank of Chicago). At Diamond Bank Limited, he was General Manager and Head of Divisions responsible for Corporate Banking, Commercial and Consumer Banking, Treasury, Investment Banking, Energy Unit, Project Finance, Public Sector, Private Banking, Strategic Planning, Financial Control, Risk Management and Systems/Technology.   

He contributed to major innovations in the Nigerian banking industry and was involved in national policy development as a pioneer member of the Nigerian Economic Summit Group and the Technical Committee of Nigeria’s Vision 2010 project.

Mr. Orji is currently Chairman/CEO of Centennial Capital Limited and Director of several companies.

February
UBA Ghana launches Ruby Account.

UBA has introduced a new product specially modeled for discerning  women of class christened Ruby Account at the plush Movenpick Ambassador Hotel In Accra,Ghana.

Launching the product, MD/CEO Mrs. Abiola Bawuah espoused  that the  product was tailored towards women because generally, women have a prudent of savings culture because of the “dependency of the family on them” “ women are becoming financially independent; women are taking up high positions in institutions; more women are becoming entrepreneurs, she added.

The new Product comes in two features, the Ruby Classic, which requires an account opening with a  GH¢2,000.00 as a minimum opening balance and Ruby Premier which requires GH¢5,000.00 as its minimum opening balance.

The accounts attract zero COT, access to consumer credit facilities, access to numerous discounts at various partner shops/ outlets/concierges  nationwide.

The well attended  launch  welcomed female politicians, seasoned entertainment executives ,business women, entrepreneurs  who are customers of the bank and senior women reporters from the media as its guests.

12
February
UBA GHANA Wins at Annual CEO Awards Night

UBA Ghana was adjudged the African Country with the highest Absolute PBT figure recently at the annual UBA CEO Awards which was held on Saturday February 8, 2014 at the prestigious Eko Hotel Lagos.

The GMD/CEO, Mr. Philips Uduoza, in his remarks opined that the awards ceremony was most deserving because of the hard work and dedication to duty by staff members during the year. “It is only proper for us to gather and publicly celebrate our star performers in the presence of all stakeholders and customers who have been a pillar of support” he enthused.

Mr Uduoza, who gave out letters of commendation plaques and cash reward of $5,000 USD to the award recipients, noted that the event was part of the best place-work policy and people strategy of the UBA Group geared towards engaging, motivating and rewarding employees.

Responding on behalf of the award recipients, Regional Bank Head, Akwa Ibom, Chukwuekezie Magnus, commended the board and management for placing premium on its people. UBA is one of the best places to work because its employment policies are non-discriminatory, and has in place a clear commendation and rewards system that motivates staff to excel, he added.

The ceremony witnessed the presence of captains of industry, customers and friends of the bank. Top Nigerian and Africa Entertainers, including Ghanaian /UK based ARTIST Fuse ODG of the Azonto fame, P-square, Banky W, Tiwa Savage, thrilled the packed Audience with music.

15
January
INTRODUCTION OF UBA GHANA INCUMBENT MANAGING DIRECTOR: MRS. ABIOLA BAWUAH

UBA Ghana’s new Managing Director/Chief Executive Officer Mrs. Abiola Bawuah began her new role with great zeal and promise from January 1, 2014.

Mrs. Bawuah joined UBA Ghana on March 1, 2013 as the Deputy Managing Director and has already contributed immensely to the performance of the Bank. Abiola Bawuah, being UBA Ghana’s first Ghanaian, as well as, first female MD/CEO, brings a wealth of local flair, finesse and know how, coupled with her enormous banking experience.

Before her appointment with UBA, Mrs. Bawuah was an Executive Director at Zenith Bank. She previously held the positions of General Manager Marketing and Group Head Retail Banking.  Before joining Zenith Bank she worked at Standard Chartered Bank as a Business Financial Manager; Cal Bank as a Senior Financial Analyst and at Strategic African Securities as an Authorized Dealing Officer/ Broker.  Mrs. Bawuah holds a BSc in Actuarial Science, an LLB, an EMBA (Finance) from University of Ghana, as well as numerous leadership qualifications from HarvardBusinessSchool, Columbia, INSEAD and Institut Villa Pierrefeu in Switzerland. UBA Ghana has gained a consummate banker and a key asset.

We believe that with the experience she has garnered through her illustrious banking career, she would take UBA Ghana to higher levels.

As she commences her tenure as the MD/CEO she has 3 main goals for the Bank;

1.    Taking UBA Ghana to new heights

2.    Exceeding customer’s expectations – with improved service delivery

3.    Greater focus on UBA’s Core values  - (H.E.I.R – Humility, Empathy, Integrity and Resilience)

Mrs. Bawuah said “UBA Ghana in 2014 will be driven by a diligent focus on our core values and in so doing the achievement of the first and second goals will be effortless, as we all humble ourselves to serve with excellence, empathize with our customers, and work to make the bank the premier banking institution in Ghana whilst doing so with integrity and every effort we can muster”

The former MD/CEO, Mr. Oliver Alawuba, following a successful stint in Ghana, has been elevated to the position of CEO West Africa, with the mandate of overseeing UBA’s business in Ghana, Cote d’Ivoire, Burkina Faso, Senegal, Guinea (Conakry), Liberia, Benin and Sierra Leone.
